page.title: 02OVERY HARBOUR
page.content: In the harbour boats of all kinds achor in the boat yard: fishing boats, ferries, speed boats and others. Under the harbour are a few ship wrecks. In winter all the boats are pulled into harbour in case strong winds and ice smash the boats together. At high tide fishermen go fishing far out in the sea to catch a lot of fish. Some dangers are at the bank of the harbour. People will fall in. There are ship wrecks and when the tide is in people can't walk across the harbour because the current will pull them under and they will drown. At low tide people can walk across the creek because the water is only ankle deep. The creek is very dangerous and Mr. Peter Back the Coast Guard is always on the look out.
